raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  name: gevent
  version: "25.9.1"
  sha256: adf9cd552de44a4e6754c51ff2e78d9193b7fa6eab123db9578a210e657235dd

package:
  name: ${{ name|lower }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/${{ name[0] }}/${{ name }}/${{ name }}-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: ${{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  script:
    - if: unix
      then: export GEVENTSETUP_EMBED=0
    - ${{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vvv

requirements:
  build:
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then:
        - python
        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
        - cffi >=1.17.1
        - cython >=3.0.11
    - ${{ compiler('c') }}
    - ${{ stdlib("c") }}
    - if: unix
      then: make
  host:
    - cffi >=1.17.1
    - cython >=3.0.11
    - pip
    - setuptools >=40.8.0
    - greenlet >=3.0.3
    - python
    - if: unix
      then:
        - libev
        - libuv
        - c-ares
  run:
    - cffi >=1.17.1
    - python
    - greenlet >=3.1.1
    - zope.event
    - zope.interface
    - setuptools

tests:
  - python:
      pip_check: true
      imports:
        - gevent
        - gevent.libev
        - gevent.libuv
        - gevent.resolver
  - script:
      - python -m gevent.tests test__util.py test__monkey.py test__thread.py

about:
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Coroutine-based network library
  description: |
    Gevent uses greenlet to provide a high-level synchronous API on top of the libev event loop.
  homepage: https://www.gevent.org
  repository: https://github.com/gevent/gevent
  documentation: https://www.gevent.org/contents.html

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - beenje
    - nehaljwani
